Groups: misc.consumers


With all the campaign talk about health care, this would be an
interesting topic to discuss.

Probably one of the biggest reasons for people not having health
insurance is that they are self-employed or do not work for a company
that offers group insurance. In effect, there is a two-tier system,
employess in groups that are considered &quot;desireable&quot;, and those that
are not part of a group and considered &quot;undesireable&quot;.

Is this a good way to go about things, or would it be better to keep
health insurance out of the office?

One of the biggest reasons that people stay in less desireable jobs or
not start their own businesses is over the insurance issue.
